{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17605877","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17605877"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:04:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:04:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15875"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15875","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15875"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.43,0.14,0.29,0.07,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8566"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64696"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8566","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8566"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15875"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50130"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"281"},{"type":"tags","id":"631"},{"type":"tags","id":"1263"},{"type":"tags","id":"1652"},{"type":"tags","id":"2036"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7061"},{"type":"tags","id":"7662"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20541"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20543"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21406"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64696","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64696"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA young man presents to his general practitioner concerned about some recent changes on his chest (Image). Apart from the observed changes on his chest, the doctor also finds an enlarged left testicle. Laboratory tests show elevated human chorionic gonadotropin levels. Imaging studies confirm the likely diagnosis and a left orchidectomy is performed. Histological examination reveals disordered syncytiotrophoblastic and cytotrophoblastic elements.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Choriocarcinoma","Embryonal carcinoma","Seminoma","Teratoma","Yolk sac tumour"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has a \u003Cstrong\u003Echoriocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E, a rare type of testicular germ cell tumour. It is characterised by the presence of both syncytiotrophoblasts and cytotrophoblasts, which produce human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG). Gynaecomastia is clearly visible.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options can be excluded: \u003Cstrong\u003EYolk sac tumours\u003C/strong\u003E produce alpha-fetoprotein but not human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG). \u003Cstrong\u003ESeminomas\u003C/strong\u003E are composed of uniform cells resembling primitive germ cells. \u003Cstrong\u003ETeratomas\u003C/strong\u003E contain tissue from all three germ layers. \u003Cstrong\u003EEmbryonal carcinomas\u003C/strong\u003E show primitive epithelial cells in various patterns.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe elevated hCG causes gynaecomastia through its direct action on breast tissue. In other cases hyperthyroidism can occur because hCG has structural similarity to thyroid stimulating hormone and can stimulate thyroid hormone production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Choriocarcinoma is a germ cell tumour composed of syncytiotrophoblasts and cytotrophoblasts that produces human chorionic gonadotropin.","High levels of human chorionic gonadotropin can cause gynaecomastia and hyperthyroidism due to its structural similarity to thyroid stimulating hormone."],"references":["Boccellino M, Vanacore D, Zappavigna S, Cavaliere C, Rossetti S, D\u0027Aniello C, Chieffi P, Amler E, Buonerba C, Di Lorenzo G, Di Franco R, Izzo A, Piscitelli R, Iovane G, Muto P, Botti G, Perdon\u00e0 S, Caraglia M, Facchini G. Testicular cancer from diagnosis to epigenetic factors. Oncotarget. 2017 Sep 18;8(61):104654-104663. doi: 10.18632/oncotarget.20992. PMID: 29262668; PMCID: PMC5732834","Chung P, Warde P. Testicular cancer: germ cell tumours. BMJ Clin Evid. 2016 Jan 7;2016:1807. PMID: 26741128; PMCID: PMC4704678","Cheng L, Albers P, Berney DM, Feldman DR, Daugaard G, Gilligan T, Looijenga LHJ. Testicular cancer. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2018 Oct 5;4(1):29. doi: 10.1038/s41572-018-0029-0. PMID: 30291251","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50130"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15875"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21232"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21232","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21232"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/VgHk58ozzfvUslvcItlJ0R7k2eQt2w.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/VgHk58ozzfvUslvcItlJ0R7k2eQt2w.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1024,"height":768}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50130","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50130"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-24T16:15:47+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-24T16:16:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8566"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64696"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/ap